Package: regridR
Title: Re-Grid Raster Layers
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: person(given = c("A.", "Marcia"), 
                  family = "Barbosa", 
                  role = c("cre", "aut"), 
                  email = "ana.marcia.barbosa@gmail.com")
Description: This package can take a set of (possibly non-equal-area, e.g. lon-lat) raster layers, and a regular equal-area vector polygon grid (such as the EEA reference grid), and transforms the former to the extent, resolution and coordinate reference system of the latter (i.e. equal-area pixels). It also includes a function to download files (e.g. variable layers) from web links, after checking if they already have been fully downloaded; and another function to build weblinks for CHELSA layers from variable names.
License: GPL (>=3)
Imports: terra, httr, utils
Suggests: exactextractr, sf
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
